ServiceAnimalRestAreas.MblShortDescription:
You'll never be too far from your furry friend with Universal Orlando's daytime kennel service for cats and dogs!

Proof of the following vaccinations is required before boarding pets:
   • Dogs: Rabies, Bordetella and D.H.P.P. 
   • Cats: Rabies, Calicivirus, Panleukopenia and Rhinotrachetitis 
All shots must be listed along with expiration dates.

Drop off in the morning as early as 8:00 am, with staff available until two hours after park close. Kennel restrictions, dimensions and requirements include:

   • First-come, first-served basis charge of $15.00 per pet, per day – no reservations required
   • Dogs weighing +39 lbs. will be boarded in our covered outdoor kennel area with fans for cooling (7' x 4', secure fencing, clean cement floors)
   • Cats and dogs weighing 38 pounds and less will be boarded in air-conditioned indoor kennel (3' x 2 1/2' metal kennel, fenced front) 

Additional restrictions apply, for more information call (407) 224-9509 or fax (407) 224-9516.
